The paper proposes a deep clustering algorithm based on a mixture of autoencoders, which involves learning a nonlinear data representation and a set of autoencoders jointly. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on image and text corpora, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of autoencoders and nonlinear data representation further suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
